labels.label: Bone
labels.definition: Predominantly endoskeletal remains. Partial bone exposure in an otherwise intact organism should be labeled "organism".

labels.label: Track
labels.definition: Impression in ground or snow made by organism.

labels.label: Scat
labels.definition: Fecal matter (not owl pellets or other regurgitated matter)

labels.label: Feather
labels.definition: One or more feathers not attached to an organism.

taxon.name: Phalacrocorax brasilianus

taxon.wikipedia_summary: The Neotropic cormorant or olivaceous cormorant (Phalacrocorax brasilianus) is a medium-sized cormorant found throughout the American tropics and subtropics, from the middle Rio Grande and the Gulf and Californian coasts of the United States south through Mexico and Central America to southern South America, where it is called by the Indian name of bigu√°.
